The article discusses the importance of making college affordable for millions of Americans. It highlights the historic investments made by the President in college affordability and quality. The article mentions the increase in Pell Grant funding and the creation of the American Opportunity Tax Credit (AOTC) to help cover the cost of tuition, fees, and books. It also mentions the President's proposal to make community college free for responsible students and to ensure that the Pell Grant is not eroded by inflation. The article criticizes the budget proposed by Republicans in Congress, which would slash investments in education and eliminate dedicated Pell Grant funding. It concludes by emphasizing the need to strengthen the economy and expand opportunity through affordable education.